##300,000 Jin of vegetables arrived in Wuhan, then how to distribute?

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The arrival of materials in Wuhan is only the first step, and it is even more difficult to distribute them to those in need in a timely, efficient and as low-loss manner as possible

By Liu Yiqin, CAIJING reporter

Editor | Sheryl Rong

At 10 am on February 16,12 lorries arrived at the Wuhan Wudong Toll Station. They arrived overnight from Ganzhou, Jiangxi Province, carrying 300,000 catties of vegetables and donated them to the Wuhan Epidemic area, the vegetables were donated by farmers in Xinfeng County and Longnan County, which are part of Ganzhou.

A few days earlier, volunteer Wang Chen, who was in charge of the donation, had successfully organized a vegetable donation, in which 15,000 kilograms of vegetables from Ganzhou were donated to sanitation workers in Wuhan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan bus driver and truck driver docking

All material donations go through the government. Wang must first contact the government, get a pass, and then unite with the various departments and organizations in need. The move came after a Wuhan Hospital posted on social media that it was running out of food, saying "staff are going into the war hungry" . As a result, most of the vegetables donated by Wang Chen this time were donated to the hospital.

In addition, Wang contacted Wuhan University's Zhongnan Hospital and Tongji Hospital, as well as the shelter hospital, which has a high demand for vegetables, and donated the rest to communities in need.

Wuhan is still under siege, and if a truck driver from another city enters Wuhan, the return journey becomes a problem. To this end, community workers helped to contact the Wuhan Bus Company and sent 12 bus driver volunteers, to take the place of truck drivers at highway junctions to transfer goods to various receiving points.

At 10:30, bus drivers with Wuhan Accents Completed A one-to-one docking with truck drivers, learning the operation of each truck, ready to go. They brought a bus, after disinfection, for the truck drivers to rest and wait. Community workers provided instant noodles, bread and hot water.

The implementation of these handover details trivial and complex, Wang Chen for this busy for several days. Wudong highway from the junction, is only the first step in the implementation of materials.

The hospital: the material confusion causes the waste easily

He arrived in a van at the central South Hospital of Wuhan University in Wuchang District, one of the designated hospitals for the outbreak. Of the materials, 5,000 Jin of vegetables were donated to the central South Hospital.

The central South Hospital alone has thousands of medical staff. 5,000 Jin of vegetables is the consumption for one day. The day before departure, Wang Chen had already contacted the hospital to take delivery of the goods. But when the van arrived, director Jiang, the hospital's director of donations and supplies, said, they've got their hands full.

On Feb. 14, dozens of lorries arrived with donated supplies, lining up on the street from inside the hospital, and staff members were busy until 1 a.m. , Jiang said. "If you have too many vegetables at once, it's easy to waste them, " he told Caijing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It rained in Wuhan on February 14 and snowed in Wuhan on February 15, making it more difficult to deliver supplies. In addition, south-central Hospital received a command notice, February 16 to focus on the treatment of a new batch of severe cases of coronary pneumonia, all those who can be mobilized were randomly mobilized to empty the ward, the isolation ward.

In addition, many of the Central South University's medical staff have been deployed to support the shelter and Thor Mountain hospitals, which are understaffed.

"since New Year's Eve, we have hardly had any rest, " a staff member at Zhongnan Hospital told Caijing. "even our students from the Medical College of Wuhan University have all come to help with material handling. "

However, because of the high consumption of vegetables, they still chose to receive this batch of supplies. Another problem is in front of them. Due to the imminent arrival of a batch of critically ill patients, many roads in the hospital have been blocked, and it takes some skills especially for large trucks to drive in, bus driver Li hasn't driven a truck for 10 years. "I used to drive a truck with five gears, this one has 12 gears. "

After coordination, the truck finally arrived at the material parking place. After waiting for nearly half an hour, a few staff members rushed to move. There are nearly 10 varieties of Eggplant, Chili, Kale, garlic, Broccoli and cabbage in the warehouse. "This eggplant is so beautiful, it will be delicious with pork shreds, " a worker said. "unfortunately, there is no meat. "

During the vegetable handling, some medical staff and passers-by soon gathered, and the staff told them not to gather together, "during the outbreak, if there is a crowd, the police will come and pick it up as soon as we are all packed up. "

A passer-by stole an eggplant and hid it behind his back.

Another staff member at the scene, Dr. Hu, told the Caijing reporter that what the hospital is most in need of right now is medical supplies, "It's life-saving stuff. We're running out of N95 masks and Hazmat suits. Doctors can only wear two layers of surgical masks and use raincoats as protective clothing. "

The 5,000 catties of vegetables will soon be finished, Hu said. He hoped the government could properly coordinate the supplies and deliver them in batches, rather than sending too many at once. They also don't have as many people to deploy, and it's easy to waste the supplies.

Community: The problem of material distribution

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wasted vegetables were left on the side of the road to be disposed of

After leaving the hospital, Wang took his driver to the Liantou Longwan community in Jiangxia District, where residents had trouble buying vegetables because of the city's closed management system.

The neighborhood had only one entrance, a narrow entrance that was difficult for trucks to enter and nearly hit the guard post at the entrance. Wang Chen and the staff helped command, and Master Li managed to drive in.

Wuhan's bus drivers are perhaps the most famous group of bus drivers in the country, known for overtaking trains on the Wuhan Yangtze River Bridge, where they often joke about taking the bus if they are in a hurry.

"They have come a long way to donate supplies, " said Li, who was traveling at 25 kilometers per hour in a truck carrying supplies. "Don't knock it. "

In addition to the community staff, there are more than a dozen owners volunteered to be volunteers, and soon empty the truck, all kinds of vegetables filled the ground, many upstairs residents in the balcony to look down.

The community workers are a bit worried, so many vegetables, distribution to each household is a problem. "If we do it tonight, we don't know how late we'll be working, and if we do it tomorrow, we don't want the vegetables to be stale. "

Finally, they decided to make a unified announcement in the wechat group of the owners, who came with a basket to pick it up. The vegetables had just come off the truck, and before they could unpack, some of the owners couldn't wait.

A male owner came to the community office and asked if he could take the vegetables back. The staff told him that everyone would be notified to collect them. The owner said there were no vegetables left in the house, and he wanted to take some back to make dinner now. The staff told him to go home and come back when he was told, and he said, "I'll be your first call. "

"I don't have wechat, " the official said, adding that the notification would be unified in the wechat group

It's a community of 2,000 people, not a large community. With the community closed management, many communities have food shortages, but the specific to each household, the situation is not the same. Some residents are more cautious and will never go out, even for free, unless they feel compelled to do so. Some residents find it difficult to go out and get supplies because of their health. Others are picky and don't want to get supplies if they don't have a favorite variety.

Therefore, even if the goods are delivered directly to the community, the final mission has not been completed. Community workers still have a lot of work to do. "We can't go door-to-door, " he said. "It's too much work, and we're worried about the risk of infection. "

At 8:30 PM, 12 trucks finally delivered their supplies, and they gathered back at the Wudong Highway junction. Twelve truck drivers have been waiting here all day. Wang, the truck driver, told Caijing that his mobile phone had run out of power.

To send away the truck drivers, Wang also had to report to government departments at all levels, collect donation information, and sort out the donation acceptance documents. So far, this round of donations has come to an end, but the community's work is not yet over.

On the morning of February 17, residents of other communities went to pick up vegetables. There was a long line at the site. To avoid contact, residents felt they were separated by two meters. At 2 p.m. , fewer and fewer residents were receiving vegetables. Because of the simple packaging and no preservation, many vegetables were discarded on the road. The staff said that the vegetables had already been damaged and had to be destroyed.

A vegetable merchant from Xinfadi, who did not want to be named, had previously donated a batch of vegetable supplies to Wuhan. The vegetable merchant set out from the Yunnan region and transported them to Wuhan by a cold-chain truck. The vegetable merchant told CAIJING that as wholesalers, more experience in the handling and transportation of vegetable materials ensures that they remain of good quality and are easy to distribute after long-distance transportation. "If the farmers organize themselves, it is more likely to cause losses. "

Today, Wuhan's Community Blockade Management is more and more strict, many Wuhan residents to "finance and economics" reporter feedback, living materials urgent. But on the other side, waste and wastage have already occurred. This requires the government to start from the source of material resources, more effective planning, deployment, timely introduction of professional enterprises.
